# User Management API

## Project Overview
This project is a backend API built to demonstrate professional-grade database integration using Node.js, Express, and Prisma ORM. The API facilitates structured data operations, allowing for the seamless management of user records within a relational database.

## Technical Stack
* Runtime: Node.js
* Framework: Express.js
* ORM: Prisma
* API Testing: Thunder Client

## Implemented CRUD Operations
This API implements the standard Create, Read, Update, and Delete (CRUD) pattern:

* Create (POST): Adds new user records to the database.
* Read (GET): Fetches and displays existing user records.
* Update (PUT): Enables modification of existing user data.
* Delete (DELETE): Securely removes records from the system.

## Setup Instructions
1. Clone the repository:
   git clone <your-repository-url>
2. Install dependencies:
   npm install
3. Run the server:
   node server.js

## Key Learnings
This project provided deep insight into:
* Synchronizing application logic with database schemas via Prisma.
* Handling asynchronous requests to prevent blocking the server.
